items.text:
Hey there! üëãüèªüòÉ

I‚Äôm Freya Tingley ‚Äî an Australian actress born and raised in Perth. I started acting at 14, taking weekly classes with a dream of one day building a career in Hollywood.

Bit by bit, I booked short films, found a local agent, and put together a demo reel ‚Äî all steps that helped me make the leap to LA just before turning 18. Not long after, I landed my first major role as a series regular on Netflix‚Äôs Hemlock Grove, followed by Once Upon a Time, Jersey Boys, and DOTA: Dragon‚Äôs Blood.

Of course, it wasn‚Äôt all smooth sailing and the journey had its pitfalls and huge learning curves along the way. But those ups and the downs gave me something valuable; an understanding of what works, what doesn‚Äôt and the exact steps to take to keep moving forward. 

Most acting schools don‚Äôt teach how to build a career ‚Äî they‚Äôll say ‚Äúget an agent,‚Äù or ‚Äúnetwork: it‚Äôs all about who you know!‚Äù - but there‚Äôs never a clear road map, or step-by-step plan to help you to make progress, no matter where you‚Äôre at that.

I‚Äôm growing a community for actors who want a clear game plan, strategy, and support to level up and turn their goals into reality.

Come hang out with us! I‚Äôd love to meet you, hear your story, and help you move closer to your dreams.

üëâ Join The Business of Acting www.skool.com/the-business-of-acting-9301/about?ref=387a46092b6b412b82c1a78a4c1a240e

See you there! üòÉ
‚Äî Freya

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union
Production Type: Independent
Project length: Short film
Project format: 4:3
Production Company: JMA FILMS 
Director: Justin Adams
Audition Location: Video Audition
Shooting Location:  Wrightsville PA
Email: Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com
Compensation: Unpaid. Food and IMDb credit only.

Synopsis: A boy won't finish his milk and so the babysitter tells him a story about a not so kind milkman

Casting information: PLEASE READ 
Character Bios:

Mrs.Anderson(Support Character)Female 35-40. Is the mother to the child.

To be considered, you MUST send your CV/Resume to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com. Do not use messenger. If you DO NOT reside in the DMV or York PA areas, we will not look at your submission unless you state you are willing to travel/lodge at your own expense. All actors will provide their own transportation.

The audition process:
1. Submit a resume or CV along with a head shot to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com
2. Please state in the subject line the name of the character.
3. If selected, you will be given sides, instructions on how to submit, and a due date.
Any questions can be sent to the Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com email.

attachments.ocrText: May be a graphic of text that says 'JMA Films "It's It'sjustpureentertainment" just pure entertainment"'

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply to advocacy groups that align with your film's message for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union

Production Type: Independent

Project length: Short film

Project format: 4:3

Production Company: JMA FILMS 

Director: Justin Adams

Audition Location: Video Audition

Shooting Location:  Wrightsville PA

Email: Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com

Compensation: Unpaid. Food and IMDb credit only.

Synopsis: A boy won't finish his milk and so the babysitter tells him a story about a not so kind milkman

Casting information: PLEASE READ 

Character Bios:

Denise(LEAD) Female ages between 30-35 is the babysitter to the child and knows about the local legend of Herbie the Milkman. 

To be considered, you MUST send your CV/Resume to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com. Do not use messenger. If you DO NOT reside in the DMV or York PA areas, we will not look at your submission unless you state you are willing to travel/lodge at your own expense. All actors will provide their own transportation.

The audition process:

1. Submit a resume or CV along with a head shot to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com

2. Please state in the subject line the name of the character.

3. If selected, you will be given sides, instructions on how to submit, and a due date.

Any questions can be sent to the Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com email.

Robercik nadal szuka do swojego filmu.

Film, o kt√≥rym mowa, a kt√≥rego negatywny bohater siƒô trzyma od d≈Çu≈ºszego czasu, nosi tytu≈Ç ‚ÄûW Sieci K≈Çamstw‚Äù. Nab√≥r do r√≥l odbywa siƒô poprzez wiadomo≈õci wysy≈Çane z adresu castingbusters2025@gmail.com i to na ten adres jest generowany pierwszy kontakt. Wiadomo≈õƒá, o kt√≥rej mowa pochodzi z dzisiejszego dnia i jak zwykle Robercik w≈Ço≈ºy≈Ç w niƒÖ trochƒô swojej pracy, ale widaƒá te≈º na szczƒô≈õcie mocne niedociƒÖgniƒôcia, kt√≥re psujƒÖ ca≈Çy trud w≈Ço≈ºony w to ‚Äûdzie≈Ço‚Äù. Ot√≥≈º, wiadomo≈õƒá zosta≈Ça wys≈Çana z adresu castingbusters2025@gmail.com. Adres ten pojawia siƒô przy okazji postu, w kt√≥rym opisywa≈Çem podszywanie siƒô Robercika pod agencjƒô Huberta Janczaka o nazwie ‚ÄûCasting Busters‚Äù. W≈Ça≈õciciel tej agencji wyda≈Ç odpowiedni komunikat, wiƒôc chwa≈Ça mu za to. Problem jednak polega na tym, ≈ºe jego agencja nie pos≈Çuguje siƒô domenƒÖ gmail.com, a swojƒÖ, kt√≥rƒÖ jest castingbusters.pl. Wystarczy tak naprawdƒô wej≈õƒá na stronƒô orygina≈Çu i zweryfikowaƒá wiarygodno≈õƒá oferty.

DrugƒÖ rzeczƒÖ, o kt√≥rej Robercik wspomina w swojej kampanii mailowej, to producenci z tytu≈Çu wiadomo≈õci. Pierwszym z nich jest producent wymieniony z adresu strony, kt√≥rƒÖ zamieszczono w oryginale tj. gdanskfilmcommission.pl. Ot√≥≈º GFC producentem nie jest wcale. Na stronie ich z resztƒÖ jest odpowiednia informacja, kt√≥rƒÖ przytoczƒô, a mianowicie ‚Äû(‚Ä¶)pomagamy w sprawnym poruszaniu siƒô po ca≈Çym Gda≈Ñsku ‚Äì pod kƒÖtem uzyskiwania wymaganych zezwole≈Ñ, wyszukiwania i dostƒôpu do lokacji publicznych oraz korzystania z us≈Çug lokalnych dzia≈Çalno≈õci z bran≈ºy.‚Äù. Przeczy to jednocze≈õnie twierdzeniu jakoby mieli oni jaki≈õ poniekƒÖd status producenta filmowego. OddzielnƒÖ organizacjƒÖ, kt√≥rƒÖ mo≈ºna uznaƒá za takowƒÖ postaƒá prawnƒÖ jest jednak≈ºe ‚ÄûGda≈Ñski Fundusz Filmowy‚Äù, kt√≥ry ma adres gdanskifunduszfilmowy.pl. Adres ten jednak≈ºe wcale nie jest wymieniony przez Roberta, co wynika z niechƒôci i braku znajomo≈õci tematu.

Kolejnym, ju≈º drugim niby producentem jest ‚Äû11 Kayax‚Äù. Ten niby producent ma nawet wciƒÖ≈º aktywnƒÖ stronƒô internetowƒÖ, kt√≥ra znajduje siƒô pod adresem https://11kayax.agency/. W ramach tej strony korzysta nawet z adresu e-mail kontakt@11kayax.pl. A czym siƒô zajmuje orygina≈Ç? Zacznƒô od tego, ≈ºe oryginalna agencja ma nazwƒô ‚ÄûKayax‚Äù i ma stronƒô kayax.pl. Agencja ta ma z filmem tak≈ºe co≈õ wsp√≥lnego, bo na stronie pojawia siƒô informacja o muzyce filmowej. W skr√≥cie ich opis to ‚ÄûManagerowie w Kayaxie prowadzƒÖ kariery artyst√≥w o ugruntowanej pozycji na rynku muzycznym, ale pracujƒÖ tak≈ºe z debiutantami kierujƒÖc i rozwijajƒÖc ich karierƒô.‚Äù, a dodam jeszcze, ≈ºe opis ten pochodzi ze strony orygina≈Çu. Swojego czasu powiadomi≈Çem ju≈º w/w stronƒô poszkodowanƒÖ o sytuacji, ≈ºe kto≈õ ich podrabia, ale niestety po dzi≈õ dzie≈Ñ nie zajƒôto stanowiska poprzez chocia≈ºby prosty komunikat. Szkoda!

W tym przypadku pojawi≈Ça siƒô jednak nowo≈õƒá, bo Robercik wyrzuca ze swojej listy adresy, kt√≥re w jaki≈õ spos√≥b nie rokujƒÖ wsp√≥≈Çpracy na p≈Çaszczy≈∫nie jego onanizmu.

items.text:
Hey there! üëãüèªüòÉ

I‚Äôm Freya Tingley ‚Äî an Australian actress born and raised in Perth. I started acting at 14, taking weekly classes with a dream of one day building a career in Hollywood.

Bit by bit, I booked short films, found a local agent, and put together a demo reel ‚Äî all steps that helped me make the leap to LA just before turning 18. Not long after, I landed my first major role as a series regular on Netflix‚Äôs Hemlock Grove, followed by Once Upon a Time, Jersey Boys, and DOTA: Dragon‚Äôs Blood.

Of course, it wasn‚Äôt all smooth sailing and the journey had its pitfalls and huge learning curves along the way. But those ups and the downs gave me something valuable; an understanding of what works, what doesn‚Äôt and the exact steps to take to keep moving forward. 

Most acting schools don‚Äôt teach how to build a career ‚Äî they‚Äôll say ‚Äúget an agent,‚Äù or ‚Äúnetwork: it‚Äôs all about who you know!‚Äù - but there‚Äôs never a clear road map, or step-by-step plan to help you to make progress, no matter where you‚Äôre at that.

I‚Äôm growing a community for actors who want a clear game plan, strategy, and support to level up and turn their goals into reality.

Come hang out with us! I‚Äôd love to meet you, hear your story, and help you move closer to your dreams.

üëâ Join The Business of Acting www.skool.com/the-business-of-acting-9301/about?ref=387a46092b6b412b82c1a78a4c1a240e

See you there! üòÉ
‚Äî Freya

Casting for people with stories of how a train journey changed their life for the better.
Did you take a trip that led to a major career shift, a new passion, or a fundamental change in your perspective? 
Have you had a pivotal meeting or experience on a train that lead that altered your life's trajectory? ( eg: you met your business partner, or had an epiphany that lead to a major life decision)

We want to hear about the journey, the moment and how your life is different today because of that one trip.

Please send email to hello@casscasting.com with some photos of you, a few sentences about your story and your availability 17th or 18th November. Fees paid to you if selected ¬£750 which includes shoot day and social usage.

items.text:
HOLDING PATTERN: A film noir by Nico Guin from Denver School of the Arts‚Äô VCA department!
Looking for 3 actors for a 5-minute film-noir!When a wealthy business woman meets a new love interest, she puts him to the test through a private investigator to find out if he can be trusted. 
Roles are not paid or promised.

ESTELLE - The younger wealthy business woman who is in love with John. She wants to test his potential as a love interest, but things take a turn. Estelle is cold, harsh, and confident, while also being sympathetic and unsettling.
JOHN -  John, a younger man who spends whatever money he has at the bar, who has been dating Estelle for a few months and really likes her. Unfortunately, when presented by Victor with the option to steal her fortune in the form of stocks and bonds, he decides the money is too enticing to decline, leading to his ultimate demise. 
VICTOR - The mysterious private investigator hired by Estelle to test whether or not John can be trusted as her future partner. He is ambiguous yet seemingly trustworthy to John, and offers him the job to steal Estelle‚Äôs assets.

We will be shooting during the first 3 weekends of November, and are pretty flexible with time of day! 
If you are interested or have any questions, you can reach out to me at 914900@dpsk12.net or 720-255-2717. Thank you!

items.text:
Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch EINE hobbym√§√üige SCHAUSPIELERIN (w/d) f√ºr unser neues Projekt! Es wird sp√§ter noch ein Buch zur Staffel geben.

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :) Fahrtkosten k√∂nnen leider nicht √ºbernommen werden, aber f√ºr Spa√ü, Speis und Trank ist nat√ºrlich gesorgtüòä

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Bereits 12 Darsteller*innen + 2 Hunde sind Teil des Teams. Die Truppe scheint ganz lustig zu sein und einige Mitglieder kenne ich auch schon l√§nger.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch EINE hobbym√§√üige SCHAUSPIELERIN (w/d) f√ºr unser neues Projekt! Es wird sp√§ter noch ein Buch zur Staffel geben.

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :) Fahrtkosten k√∂nnen leider nicht √ºbernommen werden, aber f√ºr Spa√ü, Speis und Trank ist nat√ºrlich gesorgtüòä

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Bereits 12 Darsteller*innen + 2 Hunde sind Teil des Teams. Die Truppe scheint ganz lustig zu sein und einige Mitglieder kenne ich auch schon l√§nger.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

items.text:
# **CASTING CALL** (english version below)

Hey, wir suchen Schauspieler*innen f√ºr unseren Low-Budget-Studenten-Kurzfilm. Bei Interesse kontaktiert uns bitte per E-Mail: **[LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com](mailto:LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com)**.

Der Film wird an verschiedenen Locations gedreht, daher solltet ihr √ºber einen l√§ngeren Zeitraum (**mindestens eine Woche am St√ºck**) verf√ºgbar sein. 

**Unterk√ºnfte, Anfahrt und Verpflegung werden gestellt.**

** **

** **
## **Gesucht wird:**

**weiblich gelesene Person (S√§nger*in / Schauspieler*in)**

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**
* Musikalischer Hintergrund erforderlich (Sie sollten Gesangserfahrung und wenn m√∂glich Erfahrung mit dem Klavier haben) 
* Autof√ºhrerschein
* Deutsche Sprache C1

 

**M√§nnlich gelesene Person (Schauspieler*in)**

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**
* Autof√ºhrerschein
* Deutsche Sprache C1

 

**Drehtage:**

Anfang bis Mitte Januar

 

**Handlung:**

Die S√§ngerin Liv k√§mpft mit ihrer stagnierenden Karriere. Nachdem sie vor einem ihrer Auftritte zusammengebrochen ist, nimmt sie sich eine Auszeit mit ihrem Freund.

W√§hrend er glaubt, ihren Traum zu retten, versucht sie, sich von dem zu befreien, was aus diesem Traum geworden ist.

 

 

## **ENGLISH VERSION**

Hey, we are looking for actors for our low-budget student short film. If you are interested, please contact us by email: **LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com**.

The film will be shot at various locations, so you should be available for an extended period of time (at least one week at a time). 

**Accommodation, travel, and meals will be provided.**

 

 
## **We are looking for:**

**Actress/ Singer**

Aged 20-35

**Requirements:**
* Musical background required (you should have singing experience and, if possible, experience with the piano) 
* Driver's license
* German language C1

 

**Actor**

Aged 20-35

**Requirements:**
* Driver's license
* German language C1

 

**Shooting days:**

Early to mid-January

 

**Plot:**

Singer Liv is struggling with her stagnating career. After collapsing before one of her performances, she takes some time off with her boyfriend.

While he believes he is saving her dream, she is trying to free herself from what has become of that dream.

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**

Anfang bis Mitte Januar

 

**Handlung:**

Die S√§ngerin Liv k√§mpft mit ihrer stagnierenden Karriere. Nachdem sie vor einem ihrer Auftritte zusammengebrochen ist, nimmt sie sich eine Auszeit mit ihrem Freund.

W√§hrend er glaubt, ihren Traum zu retten, versucht sie, sich von dem zu befreien, was aus diesem Traum geworden ist.

 

 

## **ENGLISH VERSION**

Hey, we are looking for actors for our low-budget student short film. If you are interested, please contact us by email: **LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com**.

The film will be shot at various locations, so you should be available for an extended period of time (at least one week at a time). 

**Accommodation, travel, and meals will be provided.**

 

 
## **We are looking for:**

**Actress/ Singer**

Aged 20-35

**Requirements:**

* Driver's license
* German language C1

 

**Actor**

Singer Liv is struggling with her stagnating career. After collapsing before one of her performances, she takes some time off with her boyfriend.

While he believes he is saving her dream, she is trying to free herself from what has become of that dream.

items.text:
Part 2: The Things We Never Said

We didn‚Äôt move for a while.
Just stood there, half lost between the noise of the city and the silence of our own thoughts.

Then her phone rang ‚Äî a soft sound that felt louder than the traffic. She hesitated before answering.

> ‚ÄúHello?‚Äù
‚Ä¶
‚ÄúYeah, I‚Äôm fine. I‚Äôll be there soon.‚Äù

When she hung up, her eyes told a story her lips wouldn‚Äôt.

> ‚ÄúYou should go,‚Äù I said quietly.

She looked at me, and for the first time, her voice cracked.

> ‚ÄúI wasn‚Äôt supposed to see you tonight. But maybe I needed to.‚Äù

The wind picked up ‚Äî or maybe it was just the sound of everything changing.

> ‚ÄúThere‚Äôs a lot I should‚Äôve said back then,‚Äù she whispered.
‚ÄúAnd a lot I shouldn‚Äôt have.‚Äù

I smiled, trying to hide the ache. ‚ÄúSome stories don‚Äôt need closure. They just need peace.‚Äù

She took a step closer. Close enough for me to see the tears she tried to hide.

> ‚ÄúAnd if fate gives us another turn?‚Äù she asked.

I looked at her ‚Äî really looked. ‚ÄúThen maybe it‚Äôll be the right one this time.‚Äù

She smiled sadly, then turned away.
And just like that‚Ä¶ she was gone.

The city didn‚Äôt pause this time. It just carried on ‚Äî like it always does.

- Migo Palendrom  write up

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union
Production Type: Independent
Project length: Short film
Project format: 4:3
Production Company: JMA FILMS 
Director: Justin Adams
Audition Location: Video Audition
Shooting Location:  Wrightsville PA
Email: Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com
Compensation: Unpaid. Food and IMDb credit only.

Synopsis: A boy won't finish his milk and so the babysitter tells him a story about a not so kind milkman

Casting information: PLEASE READ 
Character Bios:

Resident's Wife(Support)Female 35-40. in the flashback scene from 50s

To be considered, you MUST send your CV/Resume to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com. Do not use messenger. If you DO NOT reside in the DMV or York PA areas, we will not look at your submission unless you state you are willing to travel/lodge at your own expense. All actors will provide their own transportation.

The audition process:
1. Submit a resume or CV along with a head shot to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com
2. Please state in the subject line the name of the character.
3. If selected, you will be given sides, instructions on how to submit, and a due date.
Any questions can be sent to the Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com email.

attachments.ocrText: May be a graphic of text that says 'JMA Films "It's It'sjustpureentertainment" just pure entertainment"'

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply to advocacy groups that align with your film's message for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

üé∂Offering Free Acting Coachings for All Levels!üé∂

Hi! I'm Colleen and I'm a private voice & acting teacher, and the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We are currently offering free VIRTUAL lessons to meet new students who may be interested in continuing professional individualized coaching!

We currently offer lessons in voice, piano, violin, viola, cello, guitar, and acting, along with 2 in-person recitals each year in 4 Midwestern states. Each of our teachers is committed to providing personalized instruction to help every student reach their goals. Whether you‚Äôre preparing for auditions, trying to book professional gigs, or simply looking to grow as a performer, our teachers are here to support and encourage you every step of the way!

If you‚Äôd like to get started, fill out this form, and we‚Äôll match you with the teacher who‚Äôs the best fit for your goals and interests. [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

items.text:
Don‚Äôt forget to grab your tickets!

Georgetown Little Theatre proudly presents ***A Telling of The Christmas Carol*** ‚Äî running **November 27th to December 6th, 2025**.

This isn‚Äôt your average Christmas Carol‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs a witty, fast-paced, and heartfelt reimagining of the holiday classic. Ebenezer Scrooge still faces ghosts, regrets, and redemption, but along the way you‚Äôll be treated to:
Laughs, Ghosts who bicker like overworked employees, Marley fumbling through haunting ‚Äúprotocols‚Äù And the timeless spirit of generosity and hope.

You might laugh, you might cry ‚Äî but one thing is certain: you‚Äôll have a fantastic time!

**62% sold out! ‚Äî don‚Äôt wait!** 

Support local theatre
Support our amazing performers
Support the arts in our community

Tickets are on sale now ‚Äî get yours before they‚Äôre gone!

Georgetown Little Theatre proudly presents ***A Telling of The Christmas Carol*** ‚Äî running **November 27th to December 6th, 2025**.

This isn‚Äôt your average Christmas Carol‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs a witty, fast-paced, and heartfelt reimagining of the holiday classic. Ebenezer Scrooge still faces ghosts, regrets, and redemption, but along the way you‚Äôll be treated to:
Laughs, Ghosts who bicker like overworked employees, Marley fumbling through haunting ‚Äúprotocols‚Äù And the timeless spirit of generosity and hope.

You might laugh, you might cry ‚Äî but one thing is certain: you‚Äôll have a fantastic time!

**62% sold out! ‚Äî don‚Äôt wait!**

‚ú® Ihr exklusives Shooting 2025 ‚Äì Erinnerungen, die bleiben ‚ú®
üì∏ Zwei Wunsch-Themen. Ein Profi-Team. Unvergessliche Bilder.

Ob f√ºr ihre Familie, ihren Partner, f√ºr sie selbst, ihr Business-Profil oder f√ºr eine Modelmappe:
Ein professionelles Shooting ist mehr als nur Fotos. Es ist ein Erlebnis, das man sp√ºrt‚Ä¶ und dann nat√ºrlich auch sieht!

Michael Diehl ist renommierter Fotograf aus Esslingen mit jahrzehntelanger Erfahrung in seinem stylischen Studio oder auf Location, mit dem Blick f√ºr das Besondere und der Gabe, jede Pers√∂nlichkeit zum Strahlen zu bringen.

Dinah Zahran ist BeautyCreator Visagistin mit Feingef√ºhl und Meisterhand. Sie hat das Auge f√ºrs Detail und ein Gesp√ºr daf√ºr, das Beste in ihnen hervorzuheben. Sie schminkt und stylt die Haare typgerecht und passend zum Outfit. Sie sorgt daf√ºr, dass sie sich wohl, sch√∂n und authentisch f√ºhlen.

Zusammen sind sie ein eingespieltes Team und schaffen eine Atmosph√§re, in der sie sich fallen lassen k√∂nnen: entspannt, herzlich und voller Energie.
Keine steifen Posen, kein k√ºnstliches L√§cheln, daf√ºr echte Momente und viel gute Laune.

üìÖ Termine ‚Äì limitierte Pl√§tze:
14.‚Äì16. November 2025 (Fr‚ÄìSo)
21.‚Äì23. November 2025 (Fr‚ÄìSo)
Slots: 10‚Äì12 Uhr | 13‚Äì15 Uhr | 16‚Äì18 Uhr
(Nur 18 Pl√§tze ‚Äì wenn weg, dann weg.)

üíÑ Das erwartet Sie:
- Typgerechtes Hair & Make-up (ca. 45 min) von Dinah
- 1-2 Stunden Shooting mit 2 Wunsch-Themen ihrer Wahl
- Hochaufl√∂sende Bilder ohne Wasserzeichen (Farbe, getont oder s/w)
- Professionelle Bearbeitung von je 1 Bild pro Thema nach Wahl
- Alle Nutzungsrechte f√ºr private & gesch√§ftliche Eigenpr√§sentation (Social Media, LinkedIn, Xing, Modelagenturen etc.)
- Das Styling mit entsprechender Mode sind ihre Lieblingsoutfits aus ihrem Kleiderschrank. Auf Wunsch helfen wir ihnen im Studio dann gerne bei der entsprechenden Zusammenstellung.

üéÅ Perfekt als Weihnachtsgeschenk:
F√ºr sie selbst, f√ºr ihren Lieblingsmenschen, f√ºr ihren Business-Headshot, ihre Fashion- oder Beauty-Portr√§ts, f√ºr ihr Modelbook oder einfach nur was sch√∂nes und sinnliches unterm Weihnachtsbaum ‚Äì alles ist m√∂glich.

Auch als Gutschein bis 23.12.25 verf√ºgbar.

Alles inklusive: 450 ‚Ç¨ zzgl. MwSt.

‚ú® Ihr exklusives Shooting 2025 ‚Äì Erinnerungen, die bleiben ‚ú®
üì∏ Zwei Wunsch-Themen. Ein Profi-Team. Unvergessliche Bilder.

Ob f√ºr ihre Familie, ihren Partner, f√ºr sie selbst, ihr Business-Profil oder f√ºr eine Modelmappe:
Ein professionelles Shooting ist mehr als nur Fotos. Es ist ein Erlebnis, das man sp√ºrt‚Ä¶ und dann nat√ºrlich auch sieht!

Michael Diehl ist renommierter Fotograf aus Esslingen mit jahrzehntelanger Erfahrung in seinem stylischen Studio oder auf Location, mit dem Blick f√ºr das Besondere und der Gabe, jede Pers√∂nlichkeit zum Strahlen zu bringen.

Dinah Zahran ist BeautyCreator Visagistin mit Feingef√ºhl und Meisterhand. Sie hat das Auge f√ºrs Detail und ein Gesp√ºr daf√ºr, das Beste in ihnen hervorzuheben. Sie schminkt und stylt die Haare typgerecht und passend zum Outfit. Sie sorgt daf√ºr, dass sie sich wohl, sch√∂n und authentisch f√ºhlen.

Zusammen sind sie ein eingespieltes Team und schaffen eine Atmosph√§re, in der sie sich fallen lassen k√∂nnen: entspannt, herzlich und voller Energie.
Keine steifen Posen, kein k√ºnstliches L√§cheln, daf√ºr echte Momente und viel gute Laune.

üìÖ Termine ‚Äì limitierte Pl√§tze:
14.‚Äì16. November 2025 (Fr‚ÄìSo)
21.‚Äì23. November 2025 (Fr‚ÄìSo)
Slots: 10‚Äì12 Uhr | 13‚Äì15 Uhr | 16‚Äì18 Uhr
(Nur 18 Pl√§tze ‚Äì wenn weg, dann weg.)

üíÑ Das erwartet Sie:
- Typgerechtes Hair & Make-up (ca. 45 min) von Dinah
- 1-2 Stunden Shooting mit 2 Wunsch-Themen ihrer Wahl
- Hochaufl√∂sende Bilder ohne Wasserzeichen (Farbe, getont oder s/w)
- Professionelle Bearbeitung von je 1 Bild pro Thema nach Wahl
- Alle Nutzungsrechte f√ºr private & gesch√§ftliche Eigenpr√§sentation (Social Media, LinkedIn, Xing, Modelagenturen etc.)
- Das Styling mit entsprechender Mode sind ihre Lieblingsoutfits aus ihrem Kleiderschrank. Auf Wunsch helfen wir ihnen im Studio dann gerne bei der entsprechenden Zusammenstellung.

üéÅ Perfekt als Weihnachtsgeschenk:
F√ºr sie selbst, f√ºr ihren Lieblingsmenschen, f√ºr ihren Business-Headshot, ihre Fashion- oder Beauty-Portr√§ts, f√ºr ihr Modelbook oder einfach nur was sch√∂nes und sinnliches unterm Weihnachtsbaum ‚Äì alles ist m√∂glich.

Auch als Gutschein bis 23.12.25 verf√ºgbar.

üí∞ Preis:
Alles inklusive: 450 ‚Ç¨ zzgl. MwSt.

Scenic Outdoor Theatre are casting Elves and/or Mrs Claus for their Christmas event based in Stoke.
* 13th November - 24th December (Do not need to commit to all dates)
* Times: 9am - 5pm/7pm (Date depending)
* Rehearsal is 7th/8th December
* 3 breaks through the day
* Above equity pay (per per day)
* Family Friend story telling grotto

Please email danielle@Scenicoutdoortheatre.co.uk for more details and to apply.

üåü Bravo, Taiem Mahmoud! üåü

What an outstanding presentation, Taiem! You truly impressed everyone with your excellent work about the Opening of the Egyptian Museum. üëè
Your use of technology was creative and professional, and the way you organized your slides showed real effort and precision. You spoke confidently, clearly, and with great passion for your topic.

We are all so proud of you, Taiem ‚Äî you are a brilliant example of how dedication and creativity lead to success. Keep shining and inspiring others! üåüüé§üá™üá¨

üé¨ **Who‚Äôs ready to help us finish this incredible film?**
The most important boxing movie of our lifetime ‚Äî ***THE FORCE: The Michael Watson Story!*** ü•äüî•

If you don‚Äôt know the story yet, check out our **press release** and some behind-the-scenes pics!

üí• **We need your help again!**

We‚Äôve got several key shoot days coming up in **November 2025**, and we‚Äôd love for you to join us as **supporting artists (extras)**:

üìç **Sat 8 Nov ‚Äì Aylesbury Crown Court**
Michael Watson‚Äôs landmark court case vs the BBBofC ‚Äî courtroom attendees & press needed.

üìç **Sun 9 Nov ‚Äì St Bartholomew‚Äôs Hospital, London**
The emotional scene where *Muhammad Ali visits Michael Watson* ‚Äî paparazzi & onlookers needed!

üìç **Thu 13 Nov ‚Äì Constitution Hill (near Buckingham Palace)**
Michael‚Äôs incredible **London Marathon** moment ‚Äî runners & supporters for the finish line!

üìç **Fri 14 Nov ‚Äì Oatlands Park Hotel, Surrey**
The infamous press conference between **Chris Eubank Sr. & Michael Watson** ‚Äî we need around 20 people to play press!

üìç **Sat 15 & Sun 16 Nov ‚Äì Tannery Studios, Woking**
Two HUGE boxing days ‚Äî come be part of the crowd and bring the energy!

This is an **independent film (expenses only)**, but it‚Äôll be an unforgettable experience ‚Äî and everyone joining will also get an invite to the **Leicester Square red carpet premiere!** üéüÔ∏è‚ú®

üìß **To join:** email **casting@magnificentfilms.co.uk with the dates you can make, and we‚Äôll send all the info & dress code.

items.text:
**Vi s√∏ger statister til fotoshoot i Kolding - l√∏nnet**

Vi s√∏ger 4 personer M/K mellem 25-50 √•r til fotoshoot med fokus p√• hverdagssituationer i vores bilhus. Billederne vil bl.a. blive brugt p√• vores nye karriereside og stillingsannoncer. Billederne vil v√¶re af vores forskellige stillinger, fx mekaniker, s√¶lger m.m., b√•de alene og billeder af flere af jer sammen.

**Vi s√∏ger dig, der:**
* Er helt almindelig, du skal passe til vores m√•lgruppe ‚Äùhr og fru Danmark‚Äù
* Har en naturlig udstr√•ling og trives foran et kamera
* Kan samarbejde med andre

**Tid: **mandag den 10. november fra kl. 8.15 og cirka 3 timer frem.

 

**P√•kl√¶dning:** Du skal m√∏de i sorte bukser og gerne en p√¶n bluse/skjorte. Vi s√∏rger for ekstra t√∏j til de forskellige roller.

**Honorar:** Gavekort til sendentanke.dk p√• 500 kr. Vi s√∏rger for let forplejning.

**Kontakt:** Send en mail til **[camy@ahvg.dk](mailto:camy@ahvg.dk)** , fort√¶l lidt om dig selv, send 2-3 billeder (portr√¶t og fuld figur) og angiv hvilken by, du bor i.

items.text:
SYNOPSIS: When granddaughter, Red, stops receiving letters from her sick grandmother she insists on visiting. Surprised, she finds a man who claims to be her grandmother‚Äôs new carer. As he continues to ask strange questions and refuses to let Red see her, she realises the man is taking advantage of her poor grandmother, using medicines to make her sicker. When confronted the man becomes enraged and is forced to kill little Red. 

Wanted: 2 actors (1 x M, 1 x F) for exciting new short film ‚ÄòIn His Care‚Äô. Shooting in Hertfordshire, w/c 24th November, student project from an award-winning Film & TV course.

- RED (Female, 24 ‚Äì 30)

- Description: Mid to late 20s

Red is a simple, reserved girl. She is kind and holds herself highly. But when it comes to her grandma, she is extremely protective, fierce even. She is perceptive and head strong and will do anything to find what‚Äôs happening at grandma‚Äôs house.

- Height: 5‚Äô5 ‚Äì 5‚Äô9

- Appearance: Red is a modest girl. She dresses simple when visiting her grandmother, always wearing the infamous red scarf that her grandmother gave her.

- Pay Category: travel expenses and food covered

- HARRY (Male, 35 - 50)

- Description: Mid 30s to 50

Harry is carer to Ruth, conniving and manipulative; calculated and dominating. He knows what he wants and how to get it. He isn‚Äôt a smart perpetrator but rather simple-minded praying on those who can‚Äôt defend themselves and has no one to defend them. He has been getting away with it until a young girl with a fiery soul starts to uncover his secret.

Height: Tall (6ft approx.)

- Appearance: Harry is a seemingly ordinary guy on the outside. Charismatic, confident, tall, handsome, well kept. If you walked past him down the street, he may smile or wink at you. He uses his looks and caring fa√ßade as leverage.

- Pay category: travel expenses and food covered

If you‚Äôre interested, please submit showreels and any enquiries to sheldonkieran4@gmail.com by 7th November

STIRLING MANAGEMENT ACTORS AGENCY PRESENTS:

ACTING FOR SCREEN ONLINE INTENSIVE
A 14 HOUR NTENSIVE TRAINING PACKAGE DELIVERED TO YOU ONLINE ACROSS 7 MODULES - 2 HOURS EACH.

Modules:

Module One: Belief and Memory - MONDAY 17th NOVEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Two: Emotions - TUESDAY 18th NOVEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Three: Comedy - MONDAY 24th NOVEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Four: Movement/Hotseating - TUESDAY 25th NOVEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Five: Characterisation/Roleplay - MONDAY 1st DECEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Six: Audition Techniques - TUESDAY 2nd DECEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Seven: Self-Taping and Camera Work - SUNDAY 7th DECEMBER 18:30-20:30

WHAT TO EXPECT:

During these sessions you will work with both script and devised improvisation.

Woven throughout each module is insight to real industry knowledge

Our sessions will be 2 hours each

Skills Based hour

Devising and Performance hour

Feedback tailored to YOU is imperative within our course

Small cohorts allow each delegate the chance to have direct feedback tailored to them.

A Friendly, professional environment with zero judgment

Our sessions are taught by Stirling Management Actors Agency's - Artistic Director: Nathan Wedge

Your final session will also be observed by our Lead Talent Agent - Carly

Many of Stirling's past students have gone on to appear in TV Soaps, TV Series, Film and Commercial.

Book Now to avoid disappointment - FURTHER DATES WILL BE ANNOUNCED IN 2026.

SPECIAL PRICE: ¬£70 + Booking Fee

(Gives you access to all 7 modules - works out to ONLY ¬£5 per hour! )

Course Requirements:

Access to a computer with camera and microphone
Stable internet connection

Course Material:

All scripts that are to be used within the seven week course will be emailed to you clearly labelled which module they are for ahead of the course start date 17th November.

There is no need to learn the material sent, although if you want to familirise yourself with the content please do!

Who Can Join:
Open to all abilities

items.text:
The Foundry Acting Studio is now open right on your doorstep . 

Hollywood , internationally recognised training right in the North and open to all. 

Highest quality training around without having to travel to London , Los Angeles or New York for a fraction of the price ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ 

So message us today and book your place in the fastest growing acting classes in the country. 

Read our post below for all info ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶. 

Have an amazing day .

sharedPost.text:
Our students working on their emotions 

As actors for screen üì∫ we always have to be ready to show a wide range of emotions at any moment, so we work in class how to bring those emotions out safely. Powerful performances but knowing how to control them. 

We are a spotlight approved (highest quality in the U.K.) and also SAG (biggest acting union in the world üåç) approved and we are soon to be more. 

We have a curriculum that matches the largest schools in the world üó∫Ô∏è but for a fraction of the price. 

A curriculum that was six years in the making and tried and tested by Directors , Tutors, producers , casting agents, actors and many other industry professionals before being used. 

We have been asked to go to London, we turned it down to help those in the North as we need a real, high quality school here like those you find in London, New York and Los Angeles. So we made that happen. 

Hollywood standard training right on your doorstep. 

We have students from all over the country drive hours to attend our classes, students from other counties join our online. 

We aren‚Äôt just one city based, we are international. Higher standard, better quality and no generic ‚Äò one guide fits all‚Äô 

Plus, this is the best part . Not only do you get the highest standard training, we also make extremely high standard, professional feature films shot on some of the best equipment available and we cast our students first. 

No more boring classes for years, we‚Äôve had students come to us and say ‚Äò I‚Äôve learnt more in three weeks than four years at another school‚Äô 
No more sitting week after week, year after year and not getting work. 
We‚Äôve had students literally on major sets, with speaking roles after two or three lessons with us. 

So why go anywhere else? We are internationally recognised, we offer what the biggest and best do for a fraction of the price, we make films and cast you in them and we are right on your doorstep. 

So message us now for all locations, times ‚Ä¶.  and book your place . 

We hope to see you soon , not just in class but on the big screen üñ•Ô∏è

We're casting for our magical Tanfield Railway Christmas Experience in County Durham‚Äì and we‚Äôre on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

üìç Location: Tanfield Railway Path, Newcastle upon Tyne NE16 5ET
üìÜ Contract: November ‚Äì December 2025
üí∏ Rate: ¬£14 per hour ‚Äî Pay & Half on Christmas Eve

‚ú® Requirements:

‚Ä¢ Entry-level acting skills

‚Ä¢ Immersive performance ability

‚Ä¢ Must absolutely love Christmas!

You‚Äôll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, working alongside our Santa and Train Conductor in a beautifully themed setting.

üßù‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è We‚Äôre looking for:

‚Ä¢ Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

‚Ä¢ Friendly, reliable team players

‚Ä¢ Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

üìå Important Info:

‚Ä¢ Costume and full training provided

‚Ä¢ Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November ‚Äì exact dates TBC

‚Ä¢ Below is the confirmed list of working dates, and shift times : 

‚úÖ Shift Dates & Times

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 20 - 10:45am - 6:45pm

üì© To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: TANFIELD RAILWAY CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you‚Äôd be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you!

items.text:
Hi everyone! I have an UNPAID casting and crew opportunity in Hatfield, Hertfordshire.

The production name is 'All That We Feared'.

I'm looking for a male actor for the main role of 'Arlo Jones'

Applicants must be 16+. Playing age of around 17-21. There are no physical requirements for this role.

I'm also seeking for:

-Someone to do sound, own equipment preferably but not required. 

-Lighting, please note this will take place outside with no access to plugs. For this crew role you'll need your own equipment.

-AC, with knowledge of the following; how to pull focus, swapping lenses and general handling.

This production will be taking place on the 2nd November, 3rd November and 1 more date in November that hasn't been decided yet but will likely take place on a weekend.

This project is unpaid. Travel and accommodation are sadly not able to be covered but food and drink will be provided of course. 

This project is perfect for people who are eager to get experience and be on set. To the people who may have an issue with these terms for filming, I completely understand but sadly they are non-negotiable.

To those interested please send me an email ASAP on rdawsonproductions@outlook.com

Hope you've all had/will have an amazing day, thank you!

items.text:
üé¨ CASTING NOW ‚Äì Male Lead for Short Period Drama

We‚Äôre urgently casting for Ed Morris, the lead role in The Stuntman ‚Äî a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol on 11th & 12th November 2025. This is a student production (unpaid, with travel expenses covered) and will be shown at our university showcase and submitted to film festivals.

Story: Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. Determined to save his livelihood, he stages one final ambitious stunt ‚Äî a warm yet bittersweet story about passion, creativity, and the struggle against inevitable change.

Role: Ed Morris (Lead, 28) Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but quietly desperate as he clings to his dream of preserving silent cinema. Must have strong screen presence and emotional depth.

üé• Self-tape deadline: Thursday 30th October
üíª Zoom recalls: Friday 31st October
üìç Filming: 11th & 12th November (Bristol area)

To apply, please send your headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

(LIVE/In person open call auditions)

Date: Saturday 11/01/25 (November 1, 2025) and 11/2/25 (November 2, 2025

Time: 9am 

Location: K75 STUNT ACADEMY 13560 49th St N Suite 10, Clearwater, FL 33762

 

VUONA Entertainment is seeking experienced stunt performers for overseas contracts in China

‚Äã

Male 5‚Äô6‚Äù and above (170cm+) and Female 5‚Äô5‚Äù and above (165cm+) stunt performers of all ethnicities, ages 18+

Must be proficient in at least one of the following:

Fight choreography / screen combat

High falls

Fire burns

Wire work

Vehicle or motorcycle stunts

Acrobatics / parkour

Water or underwater stunts

Specialty skills (jet-ski, high divers, etc)

 

REQUIREMENTS:

1. Current stunt headshot, resume and demo reel (can be sent to k75stuntacademy@gmail.com, subject STUNT SHOW)

2. Must be physically fit, safety-conscious, and able to follow direction

3. Flexible and comfortable working in various weather and terrain conditions.

Day of Audition will consist of:

1. Pull ups

2. Cardio

3. Agility

4. Mat work: front and back, dive rolls, cartwheels, etc

5. Fight Choreography

6. Type-outs throughout audition 

Please bring printed headshot and resume to audition. 

Please bring your hydration, towel and running shoes 

No weapons allowed (prop or otherwise)

No work boots or sandals allowed 

No food allowed inside gym

Vuona at K75 Auditions form:

https://forms.gle/GibBXWPAu4xYfY198

Thank you 

#Stunts #Stunt #China #Choreography #Fire #Action

The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency
About Us
The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency is a proudly South African-based casting and extras coordination agency, operating since 2018. We work behind the scenes to help bring incredible stories to life ‚Äî connecting talent with opportunity across film, television, and digital productions.
Our Talent
With a growing database of over 1,000 talented actors, actresses, artists, and models, we take pride in representing individuals who continue to make us proud on some of the biggest local and international stages. Our artists have been featured in productions on Netflix, DStv, BET, and many more renowned platforms.
What We Do
We specialize in supplying background extras, featured roles, models, and performing artists for feature films, commercials, music videos, and television projects. Our experienced coordination team ensures every production finds the perfect fit for its creative vision.
Join Us
We‚Äôre growing fast ‚Äî and The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency is the place to be if you‚Äôre passionate about building a career in the entertainment industry. Whether you‚Äôre new to the scene or a seasoned performer, we‚Äôd love to work with you.
Connect With Us
Stay updated and get a behind-the-scenes look at our work:
üì∏ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/uzualsuspects?igsh=MWM2d3FmNXF6cjVkbQ%3D%3D&utm_source=qr

üéµ TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@uzualsuspects?_r=1&_d=egel63h4j3mjfm&sec_uid=MS4wLjABAAAAWOiaWrGgIELVrfc3NfwjMxiKFi0OjOa4djSWJVprzsacWyaIO60zeOV0tq0dHz6l&share_author_id=7485662607233745926&sharer_language=en&source=h5_m&u_code=ejd9916926k68c&item_author_type=1&utm_source=copy&tt_from=copy&enable_checksum=1&utm_medium=ios&share_link_id=D1EFA8BA-E31F-488B-A689-B75286575A49&user_id=7485662607233745926&sec_user_id=MS4wLjABAAAAWOiaWrGgIELVrfc3NfwjMxiKFi0OjOa4djSWJVprzsacWyaIO60zeOV0tq0dHz6l&social_share_type=4&ug_btm=b8727,b0&utm_campaign=client_share&share_app_id=1233

üìò Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/share/1BwFmaPS81/?mibextid=wwXIfr

‚ñ∂Ô∏è YouTube: https://youtube.com/@theuzualsuspectscastingagency?si=dSQDBTmepTZm2c4H

üëâ Don‚Äôt forget to follow, like, and subscribe!
Contact Us
For bookings, collaborations, or queries, reach out to us directly:
Founder: Moira McKie
üìû +27 68 499 9959

Alternate Shadows performed `Screaming Blue Murder' at Gillingham Golf Club last night to a sold out house for Halloween. We shall be performing `Screaming Blue Murder!' again one more time at Sheerness Golf Club - 7pm!

It's 1974 Frank Wagenheim‚Äôs new movie ‚ÄòFanghelsing‚Äô is the hot topic of tinsel town ‚Äì although screen idol, Max Brant & co-star Daisy White are tipped for top honours, there‚Äôs a chilling atmosphere on set that has nothing to do with it being over budget and over schedule!

Filming on location at Moreham Wood Film Studios, on the set of a crypt in a decaying abbey, Inspector Grimpole finds the blood is more than just special effects and the screams are not just in the script!

**Don't be a blood sucker and reserve your ticket - Tickets are ¬£5 and can be obtained by calling the golf club on 01795 662585. **

The evening will be nothing short of fang-tastic!

El reconocido artista circense Mart√≠n Espa√±a Cede√±o, con trayectoria internacional de m√°s de cinco d√©cadas y representante del arte circense mexicano, informa a la opini√≥n p√∫blica y a la comunidad circense internacional lo siguiente:

Durante su participaci√≥n art√≠stica en territorio dominicano, diversos elementos de su propiedad ‚Äîincluyendo vestuarios profesionales de alto valor art√≠stico y econ√≥mico, as√≠ como equipo t√©cnico especializado utilizado en su acto‚Äî fueron retirados de su posesi√≥n sin autorizaci√≥n. Actualmente, dichos elementos est√°n siendo utilizados en funciones del espect√°culo Symphony Circus, sin existir acuerdo legal ni consentimiento del propietario.

Adicionalmente, al intentar recuperar pac√≠ficamente sus pertenencias, el artista fue obligado a abandonar el lugar mediante el uso de fuerza, situaci√≥n que ya ha sido puesta en conocimiento de las autoridades correspondientes, iniciando el proceso legal pertinente para la restituci√≥n de los bienes y la protecci√≥n de su integridad y patrimonio art√≠stico.

Mart√≠n Espa√±a ha manifestado su decisi√≥n irrevocable de proceder √∫nicamente por las v√≠as institucionales, respetando la ley y confiando en que las autoridades dominicanas garantizar√°n la correcta aplicaci√≥n de justicia y la debida protecci√≥n a los artistas y trabajadores del entretenimiento internacional.

El artista recuerda que su carrera ha sido guiada siempre por el honor, la disciplina y el respeto hacia el p√∫blico y la comunidad circense global, reafirmando su compromiso con la verdad y la defensa leg√≠tima de su nombre, su obra y su equipo de trabajo.

‚ÄúEl circo es mi vida. Mi vestuario y mi equipo no son solo herramientas; son parte de mi historia y mi identidad art√≠stica. Conf√≠o en las instituciones y sigo adelante con dignidad.‚Äù

*Half-Day Social Media Shoot ‚Äì Housing Association*

 

Hi everyone! üëã

 

We‚Äôre an independent media agency, looking for a small group of confident actors to feature in a short **half-day** filming project for a well-known **Housing Association**.

üìç **Location:** Welwyn Garden City

üìÖ **Date:** ASAP

‚è±Ô∏è **Duration:** Half-day (approx. 4 hours)

üí∏ **Usage:** Digital Channels only 

üé• **Style:** Natural, lifestyle content - showcasing everyday living and community vibes

 

We‚Äôre looking for:

‚ú® A diverse mix of people, ideally aged 30‚Äì45

‚ú® Comfortable on camera, relaxed and authentic energy (not a speaking part)

‚ú® Able to take light direction and have fun with it!

 

If you‚Äôre interested, please **comment below or drop me a message** with:

1Ô∏è‚É£ A recent headshot or link to your profile/portfolio 

2Ô∏è‚É£ Your location / ability to travel

3Ô∏è‚É£ Your availability W/C 3rd November

 

Feel free to tag anyone you think would suit this too! üôå

 

Thanks so much - looking forward to connecting!

Conrad

We're casting for our magical Tanfield Railway Christmas Experience in County Durham‚Äì and we‚Äôre on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

üìç Location: Tanfield Railway Path, Newcastle upon Tyne NE16 5ET
üìÜ Contract: November ‚Äì December 2025
üí∏ Rate: ¬£14 per hour ‚Äî Pay & Half on Christmas Eve

‚ú® Requirements:

‚Ä¢ Entry-level acting skills

‚Ä¢ Immersive performance ability

‚Ä¢ Must absolutely love Christmas!

You‚Äôll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, working alongside our Santa and Train Conductor in a beautifully themed setting.

üßù‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è We‚Äôre looking for:

‚Ä¢ Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

‚Ä¢ Friendly, reliable team players

‚Ä¢ Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

üìå Important Info:

‚Ä¢ Costume and full training provided

‚Ä¢ Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November ‚Äì exact dates TBC

‚Ä¢ Below is the confirmed list of working dates, and shift times : 

‚úÖ Shift Dates & Times

‚Ä¢ Sat, Nov 29 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Nov 30 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 6 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 7 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 13 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 14 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 20 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 21 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Tue, Dec 23 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Wed, Dec 24 - 10:45am - 6:45pm (Christmas Eve ‚Äì Pay & a half) 

üì© To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: TANFIELD RAILWAY CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you‚Äôd be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you!

I‚Äôm looking for 2 actors to fill the roles for an upcoming student short film. The film is a romantic-drama / art house project, with aims to submit to many film festivals, which is ideal for those seeking experience and recognition.

Shooting begins on 19th November, if interested please fill out this audition form:

https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=n-vu-JAJv0qVDOuPU_58dxq2NKaNLXxCl1uUZsd9XHRUN1JXVUg5NkhNRjY3TTVQS0YxRFE1NFEzNy4u

Feel free to email me @ mitchellmay478@gmail.com

Below is the character briefs.

DAVID (Lead, Male)

Description: Sensitive, introspective, deeply emotional. David is a man mourning the loss of his great love, struggling to make sense of life without Thea.

Performance Notes:

Requires strong emotional range: joy and tenderness in flashbacks, raw grief and despair in the present.

Actor must be able to express emotion physically ‚Äî through movement, gesture, and subtle facial expressions ‚Äî as much of the story is told visually, not verbally.

 

THEA (Supporting, Female)

Description: Radiant, free-spirited, playful. Thea represents love, warmth, and light ‚Äî both as a living person and as a memory haunting David.

Performance Notes:

Must have a natural chemistry with the actor playing David.

Scenes rely heavily on non-verbal storytelling: laughter, dancing, touch, and shared glances.

Ability to portray authenticity and joy on screen ‚Äî the emotional anchor of the film.

items.text:
**Casting Call ‚Äì Short Thriller Film: ‚ÄúThe Call That Lied‚Äù (Independent Production)**

Hello everyone üëã

I‚Äôm an **Asian independent filmmaker** currently developing a **20-minute psychological thriller short film** titled *‚ÄúThe Call That Lied.‚Äù*

It‚Äôs a **minimal-cast** story about **two strangers who meet online** . only to fall into a dark web of deception, cybercrime, and emotional manipulation.
A film about loneliness, technology, and the dangers

üé≠ **Casting Roles:**

**Main Roles:**
* **JAMES (Male, 30‚Äì45)** ‚Äì Emotionally complex, introverted, carries the weariness of family struggles but a deep vulnerability underneath.
* **CATHY (Female, 25‚Äì40)** ‚Äì Calm, charming, mysterious; later revealed to be part of a deceptive plot. Voice performance is crucial.

**Supporting Roles:**
* **Inspector (Male/Female, 35‚Äì60)** ‚Äì Firm, analytical, skeptical yet human.
* **Police Tech Officer (Any gender, 20‚Äì35)** ‚Äì Curious, intelligent, pivotal in the investigation.
* **Child (Girl, 5‚Äì8)** ‚Äì Brief appearance (Maya‚Äôs daughter in video call).

üé• **About the Project:**
* **Genre:** Psychological / Cyber-Crime Thriller
* **Length:** ~20 minutes
* **Shooting:** 2‚Äì3 days total
* **Location:** UK (Preston / surrounding areas)
* **Format:** Festival-quality short film for online and short film circuit submission.
* **Budget:** Independent / Self-funded

This is a **passion project**, so roles are **unpaid**, but all cast members will receive:
‚úÖ Full screen credit
‚úÖ Copy of the final film for showreel use
‚úÖ IMDb credit (post-release)
‚úÖ Meals and travel covered (within reason)

If you love acting, storytelling, and building your portfolio with meaningful, high-quality indie work ‚Äî this could be a great fit.
I‚Äôm looking for genuine performers who can bring raw emotion and subtle realism to screen.

Please message me (or comment below) with your **showreel / headshot / short intro video**, and I‚Äôll share the screenplay (*The Call That Lied*) for review.

Thank you üôè
**‚Äì Krishan V Alexsander**
Independent Filmmaker | Preston, UK

items.text:
üé≠ Not your usual acting class

This Tuesday we explore what happens when there‚Äôs no partner, no dialogue, only you, the camera, and your thoughts.

Focus: The Living Monologue: From Performed Speech to Ongoing Experience
Learn to stay alive and reactive when alone on camera, to stop watching yourself and live the moment instead.

We‚Äôll also dedicate part of the class to a Self-Tape Review. Bring one of your tapes and receive focused on-camera feedback on framing, emotional truth, and what the camera actually sees. It‚Äôs an opportunity to refine your presence, understand how your work reads on screen, and take your self-tapes to the next level.

Each Tuesday we explore a new topic through both psychological and on-camera perspectives, uncovering emotional truth, presence, and authenticity.

üóì Tuesday November 4 at 7 PM
üìç Midtown Toronto
üé¨ First class FREE for new actors

If this kind of work speaks to you, sign up here:
https://forms.gle/3LqxHGM9mfAvtaoa6

üé≠ Not your usual acting class

This Tuesday we explore what happens when there‚Äôs no partner, no dialogue, only you, the camera, and your thoughts.

Focus: The Living Monologue: From Performed Speech to Ongoing Experience
Learn to stay alive and reactive when alone on camera, to stop watching yourself and live the moment instead.

We‚Äôll also dedicate part of the class to a Self-Tape Review. Bring one of your tapes and receive focused on-camera feedback on framing, emotional truth, and what the camera actually sees. It‚Äôs an opportunity to refine your presence, understand how your work reads on screen, and take your self-tapes to the next level.

Each Tuesday we explore a new topic through both psychological and on-camera perspectives, uncovering emotional truth, presence, and authenticity.

üóì Tuesday November 4 at 7 PM
üìç Midtown Toronto

üé¨** Medvirkende s√∏ges til kortfilm for **Foreningen Lige Adgang

I forbindelse med mit speciale, udvikler jeg en r√¶kke **kortfilm i samarbejde med Foreningen Lige Adgang**, der vises som en del af deres workshops og opl√¶g om **antidiskrimination **‚Äì optagelser i K√∏benhavn.

Vi s√∏ger medvirkende, der vil dele deres perspektiver ‚Äì **uanset om du har etnisk minoritetsbaggrund eller er allieret**, som vil bidrage til en vigtig samtale om trivsel, inklusion og ligestilling.

Du **beh√∏ver ingen filmisk erfaring** ‚Äì kun lyst til at bidrage til en vigtig samtale.

Det vigtigste er, at du har lyst til at dele dine tanker eller erfaringer og v√¶re med til at skabe film, der kan g√∏re en forskel.

**Fokus p√• tryghed og inkluderende deltagelse:**
* Filmene udvikles gennem workshops, hvor du som deltager har **medindflydelse og ejerskab** over processen og fort√¶llingen
* Vi arbejder med **l√∏bende samtykke**, og du godkender altid materialet, f√∏r noget deles
* **Alle medvirkende krediteres som medskabere** i filmen üé¨

Temaer, vi arbejder med:
üí¨ Hvad vil det sige at v√¶re en god allieret?
üîÑ Hvad hvis rollerne var byttet om?
üë• Oplevelser af inklusion og eksklusion
üß† Fordomme og bias i hverdagen

**Praktisk:**
üìç K√∏benhavn ‚Äì start/midt november 2025 (fleksibelt ud fra din kalender)
üïí To hele dage (ca. 6‚Äì7 timer pr. dag) ‚Äì mulighed for √©n dag eller en halv dag
ü•ó Forplejning er inkluderet

Vi √∏nsker et **mangfoldigt cast **og opfordrer alle til at melde sig ‚Äì uanset k√∏n, seksualitet, alder, etnicitet, religion, faglig baggrund eller funktionsevne.

Skriv til mig via **malene.juell@gmail.com** eller en direkte besked med:
* Hvilke(n) dag(e) i november, du bedst kan
* Gerne et billede af dig selv

‚Äî

**Malene Juell-Hansen** (specialestuderende p√• Film- og medievidenskab, K√∏benhavns Universitet)

I samarbejde med Foreningen Lige Adgang

üì¢ **OBS: Opslaget m√• gerne deles** ‚Äì kender du nogen, der kunne v√¶re interesseret, m√• du meget gerne videresende opslaget!

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply to advocacy groups that align with your film's message for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

items.text:
Casting call!

We're so excited to be casting for our female-focused feature film, Before Us!

Log line: Five strangers wrestle with motherhood and identity while, unbeknownst to them, their great grandmothers meddle from the afterlife. As their stories increasingly intertwine, the women must discover purpose from within themselves and from one another.

Genre: Dramedy
Location: Denver metro area. We're only open to Colorado-based actors for now 

Paid, non-union

This first casting call includes our leads and key supporting roles, each paying $500-$750 depending on the success of fundraising and the final shooting schedule. We plan to shoot a teaser trailer and some social media content for fundraising purposes in November, with principal photography in January-February 2026. You can see full character breakdowns and audition submission instructions here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1mi16s2oN0Gdn0KYzpTw6VKL1LIG1mytkHOXYFYM_a3M/edit?pli=1

We're casting for:

Izzy: 30, female, Chamorro (While a Chamorro actress is ideal, Izzy can be played by any Pacific Islander)

Agnes: 51, female, Chinese-American (While a Chinese actress is ideal, Agnes can be played by any actor of East Asian descent)

Sasha: 36, female, Black

Beatrice: Any age 50 or older, female, Black

Leticia: Any age 50 or older, female, Latina

Mabel: Any age 50 or older, female, Chinese (While a Chinese actress is ideal, she can be played by any actor of East Asian descent)

Man√•mko‚Äô: Any age 50 or older, female, Chamorro (While a Chamorro actress is ideal, she can be played by any Pacific Islander)

Margaret: Any age 50 or older, female, white

Foster: 29, male, any ethnicity

Please submit your audition via the form linked above by 11:59 pm on Saturday, November 1.

items.text:
Hello fellow Colorado actors. Many of you may not know that as a SAG member actors need to follow SAG rules. I have seen several violations of SAG rules, not only in our Denver market, but in New Mexico as well. Did you know that SAG rule 14 states:

A member cannot work as both a performer and a casting director, or a performer and a member of another theatrical teamster union, on the same production without the union's consent? 

Actors should not be casting directors due to a conflict of interest, as it can lead to biased decision-making in favor of their own acting career, and because the two roles require different skill sets. 

A casting director's job is to serve the production's needs by finding the best fit for a role, a process that requires a separate and objective perspective from the actor's self-interest in getting cast. 

If you know of anyone that is breaking SAG rule 14, I urge you to call or email SAG in Los Angeles and ask to speak with their violation‚Äôs department. You can also make the claim anonymously!Ôøº

SAG-AFTRA / (855) 724-2387
info@sagaftra.org
